# Elevate Digital — Brand & Design System Rules
# Drop this file in the root of any Cursor project to enforce Elevate Digital brand standards.

## Identity

Elevate Digital's visual identity is built around the **Aurora** — dynamic, atmospheric, kinetic.
Every design decision should feel: technical, atmospheric, future-ready, alive.
The dominant aesthetic is dark-first: deep navy backgrounds, white text, electric accent colors.

---

## Color Palette

Use these exact values. Do not substitute approximations.

### Primary
- Elevate Navy:     #192036   rgb(25, 32, 54)    — primary background, 70%+ of visual weight
- Elevate White:    #ffffff   rgb(255,255,255)    — all body text on dark backgrounds

### Secondary
- Binary Blue:      #0f75bd   rgb(15, 117, 189)   — chevron motifs, gradient fills, structural shapes
- Electric Blue:    #00aeef   rgb(0, 174, 239)    — accent text, badges, links, numbered elements, footer tag

### Tertiary (Accent / Data Viz)
- Gamma Green:      #00fe7c   rgb(0, 254, 124)    — signal mark, step labels, key CTAs — use sparingly (1–2 per view max)
- Violet Vortex:    #723aca   rgb(114, 58, 202)   — innovation callouts, data viz series
- Orbital Orange:   #ff9600   rgb(255, 150, 0)    — momentum/energy callouts, data viz series
- Solar Yellow:     #ffea37   rgb(255, 234, 55)   — highlight emphasis, data viz series

### Color Rules
- Navy dominates — never use light/white backgrounds
- White for ALL body text — never navy or blue text on dark backgrounds
- Electric Blue for interactive/navigational elements
- Gamma Green is the signal color — max 1–2 uses per screen/slide
- Red, pink, brown are outside the brand palette — do not use
- Generic blue (#0000ff) is forbidden — use Binary Blue or Electric Blue only

