## Layout Principles

- Default to dark navy backgrounds at all times
- Use generous whitespace — never cram content
- Asymmetry and grid-breaking layouts are on-brand
- Accent lines / dividers: thin (1px), Gamma Green or Electric Blue
- Numbered steps use Electric Blue filled circles with white Titillium Bold text
- Section dividers use a thin Gamma Green horizontal rule

---

## The Signal Mark (decorative brand element)

Two thin crossed lines in Gamma Green (`#00fe7c`), 2–3px stroke, ~15–20° angle.
Used on hero sections, cover screens, and closing sections.
Never overuse — one per major section maximum.

---

## Elevate Brand Voice (for copy / labels)

- Confident and technical — not corporate or generic
- Active voice, present tense
- Short declarative statements over long explanations
- ALL CAPS for pill badges, step labels, and the "ELEVATE" wordmark only
- Avoid: "leverage", "synergy", "robust", "best-in-class"

---

## What NOT to do

- No white or light backgrounds
- No Inter, Roboto, Arial, or system-default sans fonts for UI text
- No generic blue (#0000ff)
- No red, pink, or brown
- No centered body text
- No more than 2 Gamma Green elements per screen
- No rounded-rect card borders thicker than 2px
- No drop shadows on text (box-shadows on containers only)
